    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="549"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Snowden</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1893</hi>
                        </date>. (Received February 13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose translated copy of a
                    communication from the Marquis of Vega de Armijo, minister of state, making a
                    formal tender to our Government of the caravel <hi rend="italic">Santa
                        Maria.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>This reproduction of the vessel in which Columbus sailed in his voyage of
                    discovery to the New World is well constructed and cost the Spanish Government
                    over $30,000.</p>
                <p>The friendly considerations that induce His Majesty’s Government to make this
                    generous offer and the flattering terms employed in communicating its wishes,
                    must awaken the liveliest sentiments of appreciation on the part of our
                    Government and people.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. Loudon Snowden.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 72—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Marquis <persName type="from">de Vega de
                                Armijo</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                            >Snowden</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ministry of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName type="venue">
                                <hi rend="italic">Palace</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-01-24">
                                <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1893</hi>.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: The Government of His Majesty, wishing
                        to give an expression of its especial regard for the United States, has
                        agreed to offer for the acceptance of that Government the caravel <hi
                            rend="italic">Santa Maria</hi>, a reproduction of the one used by
                        Columbus in his discovery of the New World.</p>
                    <p>No other than the great American nation can so worthily assume the duty of
                        preserving as an object of historic interest the above-mentioned vessel.
                        This, with the other two models of the <hi rend="italic">Nina</hi> and <hi
                            rend="italic">Pinta</hi>, will remain as a precious souvenir of that
                        unparalleled and memorable expedition.</p>
                    <p>Whilst informing your excellency of the action of His Majesty’s Government,
                        it is very pleasant to me to reiterate the assurances of my most
                        distinguished consideration.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Marquis de la Vega de Armijo.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
